{"article_id":"TyvJ48nodWZAegZu","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Police fired smoke and tear gas canisters early Sunday in an effort to disperse several dozen protesters","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"who defied a curfew in a St. Louis suburb","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"where a black teenager was fatally shot by a white police officer last week .","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"The Missouri Highway Patrol said","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"that seven people were arrested","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"and one man had been shot at the site of the protest in Ferguson , Mo .","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"Missouri State Highway Patrol Capt . Ron Johnson said","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"that the shooting victim was in critical condition","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"and had been rushed to a hospital by protesters .","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"Johnson said","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"the use of tear gas was precipitated by concerns about people","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"who 'd broken into a barbecue restaurant","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"and taken position on the roof","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"overlooking approaching police .","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"Another concern involved a man","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"flashing a handgun","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"who appeared in the middle of the street","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"as armored vehicles approached .","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"Johnson says","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"someone fired at a patrol car ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"but no officers were injured .","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"`` I was disappointed in the actions of tonight , ''","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Johnson said .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"The St. Louis Post-Dispatch reported","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"that St. Louis Alderman Antonio French ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"who has taken part in demonstrations all week ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"told reporters","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that the police 's tactics `` were a lot better ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"than they could have been .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"French also said","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that he had attempted to convince people to honor the curfew ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"but some `` did n't want to be told to leave . ''","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"French later tweeted ,","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"`` I can tell you firsthand","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that some of the people","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that remained tonight","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"were armed .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Were ready for a fight .","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"And wanted to injure police . ''","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"Hundreds of other protesters had left peacefully","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"before the midnight-to-5 a.m. curfew took effect ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"but remaining protesters","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"--","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"chanting `` No justice !","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"No curfew ! '' --","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"refused to leave the area .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"As five armored tactical vehicles approached the crowd ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"officers spoke through a loudspeaker :","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"`` You are in violation of a state-imposed curfew .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"You must disperse immediately .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Failure","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"to comply","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"may result in arrest . ''","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Highway Patrol Spokesman Lt. John Hotz initially said","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"police only used smoke ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"but later told The Associated Press","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that they also fired tear gas canisters .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"He said of police efforts :","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"`` Obviously , we 're trying to give them every opportunity","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"to comply with the curfew . ''","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"As officers put on gas masks ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"a chant from the distant crowd emerged :","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"`` We have the right","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to assemble peacefully . ''","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"A moment later , police began firing canisters into the crowd .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Protesters said","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"their faces and eyes had been burned .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"Others screamed in pain .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Jayson Ross ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"who was leading the protesters toward police ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"said :","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"`` They got guns .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"We got guns .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"We are ready . ''","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"The curfew had been announced by Missouri Gov . Jay Nixon Saturday afternoon in an effort","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"to prevent the violence and looting","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"that had marred earlier protests over the August 9 death of 18-year-old Michael Brown .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"The governor also declared a state of emergency .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Early Sunday , Johnson said","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"that authorities were not aware of any looting","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"that had occurred during the night .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Stormy weather and the urgings of protest leaders made the decision","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"to go home before midnight easier for some .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"As midnight approached late Saturday ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"New Black Panther Party leader Malik Shabazz roamed the street with a bullhorn ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"encouraging people to leave for their own safety .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"`` C'mon you all ,","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"let 's roll out , ''","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Shabazz said through his bullhorn .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"`` Let 's roll out of here ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"get some rest","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"and come back tomorrow . ''","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"Nixon said Sunday morning on ABC 's `` This Week ''","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"that he was not aware","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"the police were going to release the surveillance video .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"`` It 's appeared to cast aspersions on a young man","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that was gunned down in the street .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"It made emotions raw , ''","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"In announcing the curfew ,","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"Nixon said","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"though many protesters were making themselves heard peacefully ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"the state would not allow looters to endanger the community .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"`` I am committed to making sure","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"the forces of peace and justice prevail , ''","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Nixon said during a Saturday press conference at a church","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"that was interrupted repeatedly by people","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"objecting to the curfew","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"and demanding","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"that the officer","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"who shot Brown","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"be charged with murder .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"`` We must first have and maintain peace .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"This is a test .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"The eyes of the world are watching , ''","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Nixon said .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"`` We can not allow the ill will of the few to undermine the good will of the many . ''","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Nixon 's curfew announcement came","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"after tensions again flared in Ferguson late Friday night .","depth":4},{"id":120,"text":"Earlier that day , local police identified the officer","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"who shot Brown","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"as Darren Wilson","depth":5},{"id":123,"text":"and released documents and video footage","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"alleging","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"that Brown had robbed a convenience store","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"just before he was shot .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Police said","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"Wilson was unaware","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"Brown was a suspect","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"when he encountered him","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"walking in the street with a friend .","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"Law enforcement officials tell Fox News","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"that the footage of Brown in the convenience store was released by local authorities over the Justice Department 's objections .","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"One official told Fox News","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"that federal authorities had their own copy of the tape","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"and did not intend to make it public .","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"In a statement Sunday , Justice Department spokesman Brian Fallon said","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"Attorney General Eric Holder has requested an additional autopsy of Brown to be performed by a federal medical examiner .","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"`` This independent examination will take place as soon as possible , ''","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"the statement said .","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"`` Even after it is complete ,","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"Justice Department officials still plan to take the state-performed autopsy into account in the course of their investigation . ''","depth":5},{"id":143,"text":"Johnson ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"who is in charge of security in Ferguson ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"40 FBI agents were going door-to-door in the neighborhood","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"starting Saturday ,","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"talking to people","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"who might have seen or have information about the shooting .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"Johnson assured those at the news conference","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"that police would not enforce the curfew with armored trucks and tear gas","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"but would communicate with protesters","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"and give them ample opportunity","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"to leave .","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"Nixon and Johnson were flanked by numerous local elected officials ,","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"including U.S. Rep. William Lacy Clay Jr. ,","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"who urged Johnson to be flexible with the midnight curfew .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"`` Why is the focus on security","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"and not getting justice ?","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"Why is there not an arrest ? ''","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"one women yelled .","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"Brown 's death had already ignited several days of clashes with furious protesters .","depth":5},{"id":163,"text":"Tensions eased Thursday","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"after Nixon turned oversight of the protests over to the Missouri Highway Patrol .","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"Gone were the police in riot gear and armored vehicles ,","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"replaced by the new patrol commander","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"who personally walked through the streets with demonstrators .","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"But Friday night marked a resurgence of unrest .","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"On Saturday , some residents said","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"it appeared the violent acts were being committed by people","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"who came from other suburbs or states .","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"`` Who would burn down their own backyard ? ''","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"asked Rebecca McCloud , a local","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"who works with the Sunshine Baptist Church in St. Louis .","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"`` These people are n't from here .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"They came to burn down our city","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"and leave . ''","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"Local officers faced strong criticism earlier in the week for their use of tear gas and rubber bullets against protesters .","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"Johnson said","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"one tear gas canister was deployed Friday night","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"after the group of rioters became unruly","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"and several officers got trapped and injured .","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"Wilson , the officer","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"who shot Brown ,","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"is a six-year police veteran","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"who had no previous complaints against him ,","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"the local police chief has said .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"The Ferguson Police Department has refused to say anything about Wilson 's whereabouts ,","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"and Associated Press reporters were unable to contact him at any addresses or phone numbers","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"listed under that name in the St. Louis area .","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"Wilson has been on paid administrative leave since the shooting .","depth":8},{"id":192,"text":"St. Louis County prosecutor Bob McCulloch said","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"it could be weeks before the investigation wraps up .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":387,"left":313,"right":386,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":292,"right":312,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":267,"right":291,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":239,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":232,"right":238,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":216,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","